e for disaster-prone territories to determine strategies for restructuring and redesigning their environment. This book proposes the creation of knowledge economies, whereby empowered communities may produce innovative knowledge translatable across the African diaspora.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican diaspora2DLC. 0aAfrican diaspora. 0aEconomic developmentxEnvironmental aspectszDeveloping countries2DLC. 0aEconomic developmentxEnvironmental aspectszDeveloping countries. 0aKnowledge economyzDeveloping countries2DLC. 0aKnowledge economyzDeveloping countries. 0aNatural disastersxEconomic aspectszDeveloping countries2DLC. 0aNatural disastersxEconomic aspectszDeveloping countries. 0aNatural disastersxPlanningzDeveloping countries2DLC. 0aNatural disasterszDeveloping countriesxPlanning. 7aSCIENCE / Global Warming & Climate Change.2bisacsh1 aBiracyaza, Emmanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDandridge, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHabimana, Samuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontalvo, Yeishka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoberts, Shearon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaldron-Moore, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaldron-Moore, Pamela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt2 aKnowledge Unlatchedefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099